articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

articleContent.title: How to plan the perfect road trip in coastal Maine

seoInfo.metaDescription: Cory Lee takes us on an accessible tour of Acadia National Park, Ogunquit, and beyond.

I’ve always loved train travel. There’s something special about settling into a window seat and watching the landscape drift past. And as a wheelchair user, that joy only grows when the journey feels easy: level boarding, space to move, and the kind of accessibility that lets you fully relax. For me, the best train rides—like weaving through the Tuscan countryside on Trenitalia—are never just a way to get from A to B; they're part of the adventure.

tripContent.title: Chase horizons and conquer trails across Nevada’s rugged backcountry
tripContent.description: Nevada’s wild places were made for those who move at their own pace. Wander through desert canyons, alpine lakes, and ancient rock formations, all in one trip. Whether you're chasing stars in a dark sky park or breathing deep in the high mountains, this is the untamed side of the Silver State, ready to be roamed, hiked, and discovered.

articleContent.title: How to eat your way through Greenville, SC

seoInfo.metaDescription: For those who plan their meals before booking a plane ticket, listen up: There is a place where you can immerse yourself in the dining cultures of 34 countries across five continents without leaving a single city limit. Greenville, South Carolina is much more than a restaurant hub—it has enough festivals, food tours, and dinner views to fuel a lifetime of trips. All of this in mind, it’s no wonder the region will be featured on Season 23 of Bravo’s Top Chef, and host the inaugural Michelin Guide American South Ceremony.

tripContent.title: Discover Louisville’s global cuisine at these hidden gems
tripContent.description: When it comes to your taste buds, Louisville’s lively food scene invites you to adventure beyond city limits. Plan your culinary exploration with this roundup of the city’s most-loved eateries, serving classic and creative dishes inspired by food and festivities from around the world.
